database.key_value_hazelcast

Class KeyValueTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • database.key_value_hazelcast.KeyValueTest

  • public class KeyValueTest
extends java.lang.Object
    Main class for inserting a graph schema into a key-value store. This class is mainly used as an example - the key-value store being used is Hazelcast, which is an in-memory database.

      • executeSchemaChange

        public static void executeSchemaChange()
        Main method for executing the schema conversion to Hazelcast. The method just needs to be called statically as it operates on files created during the initial schema conversion process.

      • nodesMap

        private static void nodesMap()
        Builds up the mappings in the database for all the nodes in the original graph. It reads the nodes.txt file (found in the workspace location [see README.md for more information]).

      • edgesMap

        private static void edgesMap()
        Builds up the mappings in the database for all the edges in the original graph. It reads the nodes.txt file (found in the workspace location [see README.md for more information]).
